[DhtmlXQ_comment0]op ldz c0102020402 move the advisor elephant carefully　||In this example, red started the game with the central cannon with 7th pawn advancement variation. ||Black countered with the sandwiched horse defense.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]Red chose to play the advisor for fear of black's skewer with C6+5.||While this may seem to be a reasonable move, it is not a good one, because playing A6+5 would be at the expense of the development of the other chess pieces.||Besides, playing A6+5 would seem ONLY to be able to defend against black's C6+5 threat. The efficiency of this move would be also very low and inappropriate.||Jim: Red's formation is now more or less set and black would be able to choose a target for attack.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
